Here's a funny situation: I registered for Pandora a long time ago. I get a "welcome to pandora" email today. I note the email address is the same as mine, minus the ".". I.e. I'm first.last@gmail.com and they registered under firstlast@gmail.comAs most of you probably know, Gmail doesn't allow you to register variations of someone's existing user ID where the difference is only a period, and will route any email to firstlast@gmail to first.last@gmail.So I tried logging into Pandora with the firstlast@gmail, didn't known the password. Requested my password, it sends it to MY email address, which I now log in and change it.So now I've locked the owner out of his pandora account because he registered it with my email address. Why would they possibly do that when they can't possibly own that email address?Amusingly the kid is 15 according to his birthdate.
