I suffer from a similar problem, but with my Apple ID: apparently it's popular amongst forgetful people, since I get a password reset e-mail about once a week, that I didn't request. Most of them are in English, some in Japanese, but I've also seen ones in French and Spanish.This would have been only a minor annoyance if not for the fact that Apple locks your account if there are too many password reset attempts. So invariably it ends up locked when I'm about to use it, and I have to reset it from iforgot.apple.com (I did not forget, dammit! ).In fact, I never memorized it because it's kept in my keychain. Alas, it's got even more annoying recently, as the reset interface now requires you to type in the password manually. Thank god I could bypass it by turning off JavaScript temporarily. They'd better not switch to using a soft keyboard like many banks like to use for their "two-factor" authentication. I thought I've shared my frustration before, but a quick search turned up nothing...
